Lateral line complete with 32 (2) or 33 (2) scales. Transverse scale rows above lateral line scales 4 (4); between lateral line and pelvic-fin origin 3½ (4); between lateral line and anal-fin origin 3. Circumpeduncular scales 16. Predorsal scales 9 (2), 10 (1) or 11 (1); scales regularly arranged, same size as flank scales. Chest and belly scaled. One long axillary scale at base of pelvic fin, its tip reaching posterior end of pelvic-fin origin. Dorsal-fin base scales 6 (4) of which last 5−6 attached to base of dorsal fin. Anal fin base scales 4, of which last 2−3 connected to fin base. Scales between anus and anal-fin origin 4 (4).Total vertebrae 32, comprised of 21 abdominal and 11 caudal vertebrae (
Fig. 3
).
